"{\"uid\": \"gazette-news.co.uk-news-24020746.colchester-tory-candidate-makes-olympic-comparison-election-looms\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PoliticsColchester  A PARLIAMENTARY candidate who is contesting the Colchester constituency at the nextGeneral Electionhas suggested that keeping the seat blue will be as hard as making an Olympic team.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 202, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 68, \"end\": 78, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colchester\", \"score\": 0.9999513385892689, \"rank\": 3.539663219708899e-05, \"text\": \"Colchester\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colchester\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"James Cracknell, who was selected last year to stand for the Conservative party at the next election, published a post on social media on Monday morning, which read: \\\"In an Olympic year, my goal would be clear and in my control.\", \"from\": 204, \"to\": 432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 204, \"end\": 219, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cracknell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"James Cracknell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cracknell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Cracknell\"}, {\"begin\": 265, \"end\": 283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservative_Party_of_Canada\", \"score\": 0.9897656189750383, \"rank\": 0.010323095621892752, \"text\": \"Conservative party\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservative_Party_of_Canada\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Conservative_Party_of_Canada\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"My goal is as clear this year and going to be as hard, but not totally within my control.\\\"\", \"from\": 434, \"to\": 525, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Cracknell, 51, won a gold medal in the coxless four at the Sydney Olympics in 2000 and the Athens Olympics four years later; he then retired in 2006.\", \"from\": 527, \"to\": 679, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 530, \"end\": 539, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cracknell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Last year, Mr Cracknell was a surprise choice to become the Colchester Conservatives' parliamentary candidate after Will Quince announced he would step down as an MP.\", \"from\": 681, \"to\": 847, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 695, \"end\": 704, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cracknell\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q483501\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sarah_Cracknell\"}, {\"begin\": 741, \"end\": 751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colchester\", \"score\": 0.9999513385892689, \"rank\": 3.539663219708899e-05, \"text\": \"Colchester\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\", \"Q3957\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colchester\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Colchester\"}, {\"begin\": 752, \"end\": 765, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland_Conservatives\", \"score\": 0.9999999998715339, \"rank\": 1.2622461962546824e-10, \"text\": \"Conservatives\", \"types\": [\"Q7278\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland_Conservatives\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Northern_Ireland_Conservatives\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Mr Cracknell previously contested the combined constituency of South West England and Gibraltar in the European Parliament election in 2014, but he, alongside five other Conservatives, was defeated by UKIP.\", 